rComments: good professor but never responds to emails
Super easy to understand the course material. The reviews dont do him justice. He is a good prof and marking was fair.

Lectures are quite dry and boring. Hard and rash marker for assignments and most importantly can be quite rude and condescending. If there is another prof available go with that one as Professor O'Neill is clearly not the man!

Condescending & contradictory. He only read off the unhelpful PowerPoints so I just stopped going to class and did the readings. Got As & Bs on everything and ended up with a C in the class. How? The disaster of a final that made absolutely no sense. Listen to a podcast on actresses in Hollywood and relate it to class material. Like what? AVOID!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Probably the worst professor I've had in all 4 years of my PAP and POL degree. He is disorganized, has a vague, and often times contradictory grading criteria, slightly racist and condescending, and was really hard to get a decent grade because his expectations were always unclear. I wish I had a better professor teaching this course.

I didn't know it was possible for his teaching to get worse. He does not care about his students nor does he care if we succeed. He is both condescending and impossible to reach outside of class. There is no organization whatsoever and you should expect the syllabus to change multiple times during the term. Expectations have not once been clear.

RUN!! WORST prof EVER. He doesn't care about his students. Nous devons poser nos questions sur les travaux uniquement sur le forum, mais il répond jamais. Il ne donne jamais plus de 4/5. Il est TRÈS condescendant. Les consignes ne sont jamais clairs. Il fait 5 fautes par phrase.. vraiment, c'est le pire professeur que j'ai eu en 4 ans.

In the beginning I though Dr. ONeill was an okay prof. He was a bit condescending and everything he wrote from assignment instructions to emails were riddled with spelling errors but its whatever, nobodys perfect right? All the assignments were actually relevant and made senses until the final exam. I got As and Bs on everything but straight u

one of the worst profs I have had at the University of Ottawa, he is very snobby, thinks he's amazing at explaining stuff which he is not. He says you can write your paper in whichever way you want and then deducts points for not doing it a certain way! Most confusing prof I have had and it's just annoying how bad he is.

So many written assignments, no tests or mc on the exam. He likes to discuss topics but his meandering can be very hard to follow and know what's impt when taking notes, and I feel like I leave classes with nothing written down. Inconsistently posts slides, so you have to come to class. Is super unclear with due dates, was an ongoing issue.
Never clear on instructions, most would have grammar errors. Straight up rude.

If you want a professor with clear grading criteria, clear due dates, want to know your exam schedule before December (yes, I'm serious), that is accessible, that wants students to succeed, and does not send condescending emails, do not take this "professor". The most unprofessional and incompetent professor I have had in my four years at uOttawa.

I liked Dr. O'Neill. He was engaging in a discussion format and made your comments feel valued. His one drawback is that he often isn't too specific about expectations for assignments and gives little feedback.

I've had O'Neill a few times and I really enjoy his classes. He expects you to participate and learn something, so definitely read the articles he assigns. The nice thing is, he provides everything you'll be learning about so you dont need to buy a textbook. Its worth taking his class because you'll remember the topics that are discussed.
Great prof for a seminar, but I would see why he wouldn't be so great for first or second year classes

TOUGH GRADER and you get confused by what he say! No slide and speak to quickly for you to take notes. Exams may seem easy but when you get your paper you just want to quit the class. If you have questions for your exam you gotta fill a paper explaining the reason why you wanna meet him! WILL NEVER TAKE A CLASS WITH HIM AGAIN!

Literally the worst professor at the University. Acts like he doesn't care how you do your assignments and gives "free range" then takes off marks for not including specifics that he never mentioned. No office hours, won't meet after class. University should be ashamed to even pay this idiot. Doesn't care about you or your learning.

In one 2 hour lecture, I counted him saying "uhm" 490 times. 490 times!!!! Very tough marker, lost 10% on my essay because I didnt include a marking grid. Mid Term was all multiple choice. Go with the rule "If All of the above is an option, pick it".

Very HARD MARKER with no logic. Appears intelligent but he really is not. Don't take his class if you like Politics because you might change your mind afterwards. Essays, midterm, and final extremely difficult.You have no chance to raise your mark. Take it with someone else.
An amazing teacher who really knows what he is talking about.
Other profs make fun of him because he is notoriously incompetent. It is hard to take him seriously.
it was a good class with good content. Only thing is he expected a lot on the essay
no slides. lectuers short and not useful. must RELY on the book for his class. and his TA's are b****'s

Overall pretty good class. Assignemnts are average, he's very clear and concise, answers questions and addresses problems of students. Class structure is very much aimed towards student successif you do the work.
Canadian Politics is already dry so he can't help that.  Overall, pretty nice guy.  He's not out to get you even though the assignments are tough.  He just wants your best effort.
This guy is awesome. He has that bit of sarcasm to him that is enjoyable. Plus, he uses this site at the beginning of the year and addresses comments posted here, which is neat.
Either take this class, or pour meat sauce on yourself then start throwing rocks at bears, either way it's gonna be painful.
Resign, Resign and Resign
NightMare, Horrible, Stupid, And UseLess.

the worst prof i've ever had at ottawa u. he messed up dates and events so badly, i sat next to the smart kids just to be safe. he said the charter came about in 1984, among other stupid errors. once he forgot his lecture notes and tried to improvise, but couldnt remember the topic. idiot.

Not the worst prof at UofO. Somewhat difficult marker but really, we can't all get "A"s and he's very fair if you feel your paper was not graded properly. He knows his stuff about the topic and can convey it well for such a dry topic

To start, the subject is pretty dry to start with.  The guy does a good enough job covering the material but it would be nice to hear something that wasn't rehearsed from the text. 'It's in the text'...okay.haha.  Anyways, overall he's a decent lecturer and does offer a lot of help outside of class.

I'm not sure why everyone's bashing him. I'm looking to take another course by him, but they don't show him as teaching at Ottawa U anymore, which is a shame: He was articulate, fair, and he even offered a chance for students to get their stuff re-graded (a lot of profs do this, but not as brazenly as he did). Highly Recommended.
The worst prof when it comes to marking...I think he enjoys people failing....The only thing he talks about it Quebec

The most boring class I've ever taken.  The assignments are marked really hard.  For example 'wasted space' between paragraphs.  The mid-term didn't really focus on material taught in class.  Political participation exercises were easy!
He's pretty uninterested in the subject, yet still somewhat stimulating for a dry subject.
Either drop his class if you get him or prepare to get crappy marks without any real explanation. Not the worst prof at UofO but far from being the best (or even good really).

the assignments are easy.  i find the class lectures quite boring.  the mid-term didn't even cover any of the stuff from the lectures.  really don't know what material to study when preparing for exams.
Awesome prof, by far one of my favourites. Other people don't like him as much so buyer beware. Very entertaining lectures, and very knowledgeable about his subject matter.

He doesn't help the class understand WHY they have done poorly on assignments, and he insists that any changes to marks be done through the department in totally unnecessary bureaucracy. He is very knowledgeable, but he teaches rather poorly.
Exam did not reflect class lectures so what's the point of going to class.

A TERRIBLE prof. He doesn't even write his own exams- he gets them from the textbook publisher's exam bank. No discussion groups- only the other class gets those. A really boring prof- he'll lecture for 4 hours, with only 15 minutes worth of information.
Very knowledgable - keeps the theory and the practica together - makes his poitns more interesting with humour - hard but fair marker.

Canadian politics: tedious classes; 10-20 minutes of notes and then digresses (ahh boring). Information learned in grade 9, 8 or 10.  Marks essays horridly; not clear on outline and then 'wham' you are hit with a mediocre mark.  Appalling class control.
So far so good, except he refuses to use the microphone so it's impossible to hear him.  Easily distracted, but makes for interesting side notes.  Assignments are easy but pointless.
No Comments
Most useless class ever. Bring a laptop so you can play solitaire. All he does is recite statistics that are already common knowledge. Nothing new at all. Talks a lot about his dog.

Arrogant, unhelpful and very unclear about what he wants for assignments, until you get back that is, and then it is clear in his criticism. And I got good marks, so it isn't because I'm bitter. Not very nice either.

Easy to understand and follow but he seems to have little control over the class. He'll cover material for 10-20 minutes and the rest of the class will be senseless discussion on Canadian politics. I don't mind discussion but this class just has too much.

I find him to be well versed on the subject, but the marking of assignments is questionnable.  I find him to not take the time to mark properly and he is unclear about what he wants in his assignments.  I am not fond of this class in the least.
He knows alot about canadian politics, so the class is really interesting for the people who like that subject. he is fair and a good teacher overall.
Class is boring as hell, but seems like a nice enough prof.
